oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Program from Annual Banquet, Tennessee Chapter, American Institute of Architects, 1923 October 3. Front cover.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This program from the 1923 Annual Banquet of the Tennessee Chapter of the American Institute of Architects, held at the Centennial Club, boasts a number of distinguished guests, including architect and past president Henry C. Hibbs. Henry C. Hibbs was elected as a member of the American Institute of Architects in March 1919. From 1919 to 1920, he served as a sponsor, charter member and first president of the Tennessee Chapter of the A.I.A. Forms part of the Henry C. Hibbs Papers. 1 program : col. ; 5.25 in. x 9.5 in.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Hibbs, Henry C. (Clossen), 1882-1949
